name: Study for masked portraits, A (1), 2021
description: This portrait is produced with a mixture of processes: neural net based image transform (modified pix2pix) using a model train with masked sitters who sat for my robots in Dubai and Hong Kong. A generative drawing system similar to the one controlling my robots' behaviours, multiple feedback loops and my interventions in most steps. Interestingly the video work is designed to encapsulate multiple artworks which can be extracted by taking snapshots from VLC. @patricktresset . -- 992 x 1224, 60fps video (visually lossless x264 compression).
